content:
Turn On Email-to-Case

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Customize Application permission needed.

To enable Email-to-Case:

Confirm your case page layout includes the Email quick action.
Create email templates for agents (optional).
Select a Default Case Owner and Automated Case User from Setup Settings.
Enter Email-to-Case in Quick Find, select it, click Edit, then Save to Enable Email-to-Case.
Also, select Enable On-Demand Service and Save.

Enabling Email-to-Case creates the Send Email quick action. You can't disable it after enabling, but you can update settings.

Configure Email-to-Case
